1️⃣ What is the difference between getElementById, getElementsByClassName, and querySelector / querySelectorAll?
Ans:=>
getElementById==> IDs must be unique, selects One element by its ID and Fastest method.

getElementsByClassName==> Select all the classes in the class name, updates automatically if DOM changes and Returns a live HTMLCollection.

querySelector ==> Returns First matching element.

querySelectorAll ==> Returns all matching element.

2️⃣ How do you create and insert a new element into the DOM?

Ans:=> 1. Create the Element
       2. Add content or Attributes
       3.Insert into the DOM like append(),appendChild() etc.

3️⃣ What is Event Bubbling? How does it work?

Ans:=> Event Bubbling==>Event Bubbling is when an event flows from the innermost element outward to outer container elements.

Worked it==>Button event runs,Then parent event runs,Then document,Then window

4️⃣ What is Event Delegation? Why is it useful?

Ans:=> Event Delegation==>Event Delegation means attaching a single event listener to a parent element to handle events on its children using bubbling.

Useful :->Better performance (fewer listeners),Works for dynamically added elements,Cleaner code,Memory efficient.


5️⃣ What is the difference between preventDefault() and stopPropagation()?

Ans:=>
      preventDefault() ==> Default browser behavior.
      
      stopPropagation() ==> Event bubbling.